keyValuePair.Value: That defeat must be hard to swallow. What went wrong?
You looked in complete control after the first leg. One foot already in the Final. But it all fell apart today. How do you explain a hammering like that?
We've been beaten by a better team.

I think we should have known we'd be put under a bit of pressure today. We were a little lucky to win at their place and, once they went ahead today, the momentum of the whole tie shifted. To be honest, we didn't look like we knew how to respond.
That's a disaster.

I can't offer any excuses. We did well to reach the semi-final and I thought we might have done enough to get to the Final. But we've been well beaten today. Sometimes you just have to credit your opponent.
We were outplayed everywhere.

We won the first leg and wanted to give our fans something to celebrate today. But we found ourselves completely out-fought and out-played. We can't pretend otherwise. They were the better team and deserved to go through.
Can you explain such a comprehensive defeat?
You must have been hoping for better after winning the first leg. But today your opponents controlled the game and you've been well beaten and dumped out of the competition. What happened?
Their line-up surprised us.

We knew they'd come back at us after we won the first leg. But they made changes in their line-up today and we couldn't cope with the men they were getting over in key areas. It gave them the momentum and they took their chances. We're devastated.
It's about how we respond now.

To be honest, we've been beaten by a better team today. We won the first leg but that just fired them up for this game. It's about how we learn from this. A terrible result but I want to see us respond now.
We should have been more aggressive.

I think we were our own worst enemies today. Instead of building on the victory in the first leg, we went into our shell, trying to hang onto what we'd got. We just never got going as an attacking threat and we could even have lost by more.
Why weren't you able to hang on and qualify?
Your boys had their noses in front after winning in the first leg but today I guess you were taught a pretty harsh lesson. What can you learn from this defeat?
I have to take some of the blame.
I have to take some of the blame.

We were so positive in the first leg and perhaps I should have trusted the boys to deliver again today. But I chose to go with a more defensive shape and the opposition took advantage. They steam-rollered us, to be honest. I have to take a share of the blame.

We were so positive in the first leg and perhaps I should have trusted the boys to deliver again today. But I chose to go with a more defensive shape and the opposition took advantage. They steam-rollered us, to be honest. I have to take a share of the blame.
We were desperate to go further in this competition.

Look, everyone knows we wanted to really test ourselves in this competition. But today we've learned that, even after a first leg victory, you can't take anything for granted. We've only ourselves to blame for going out.
We didn't deal with the pressure.

They're a good team but we contributed to our own downfall today. It was as if the boys thought they'd already done enough to go through. When the opposition turned the screw, though, we just didn't have an answer to it. It was a shocking display.
What do you take from such a dramatic defeat?
After the win in the first leg, your fans were expected you to go through to the next round. Instead, today, your team's been taught a very harsh lesson. Can the team's confidence recover from this?
I probably mis-read the situation.
I probably mis-read the situation.

We took a really positive approach in the first leg. It worked and that gave us the advantage. I thought we'd be able to hang on here and maybe I went with too defensive a formation. The lads couldn't regain the initiative. We couldn't get out of our half. And now we've blown a great chance.

We took a really positive approach in the first leg. It worked and that gave us the advantage. I thought we'd be able to hang on here and maybe I went with too defensive a formation. The lads couldn't regain the initiative. We couldn't get out of our half. And now we've blown a great chance.
I'm speechless about what I've just seen.
Our fans definitely deserve better than that. We had the lead. All we needed to do was stay calm and steer our way into the next round. But we fell apart here. We have only ourselves to blame.
We couldn't get near them today.

We didn't deserve to go any further. In these two-legged ties, you have to be able to defend a lead. But we played like strangers and just caved in as soon as we went behind. We've got to learn to be stronger than that. We let ourselves down.
Was it just a case of seeing the game out today?
Was it just a case of seeing the game out today?
That comfortable win in the first leg put you in a very strong position. The opposition came back at you today, but were you always confident you had enough in hand to get through?
That comfortable win in the first leg put you in a very strong position. The opposition came back at you today, but were you always confident you had enough in hand to get through?
We were the better team over two legs.

We knew they'd come back at us today. They had nothing to lose. I'm very happy our players didn't lose their heads at any point. Even when we went behind today, I knew they'd steer us through. We looked a mature team out there.
On to the next game!

Today wasn't a great display and I'm sorry we didn't put on a show for our fans. But we're through and that's what matters. The games are coming thick and fast at the moment. Let's forget this result and move on.
We can't afford those mistakes.

Of course I'm glad we're through. But I have to warn the boys. If we're as sloppy in possession as we were today, we can't expect to go much further in this competition. Our standards have to be higher than that.
Do you expect a tougher game in the semi-final?
Drawing today was all you needed to do and you're comfortably through to the semis now. What did you make of today's performance? Do you think your team's strong enough to earn a place in the Final?
All I'm worried about is our next game.

I like the mentality I'm starting to see in this team: positive, aggressive, confident. If the boys can keep playing at that level, we can achieve big things in the future. But, right now, we just need to focus on our next game.
I hoped for more today.

I think perhaps we took our foot of the gas, knowing we had plenty in hand. That won't always be good enough, though. Whoever we play in the semi-final, we'll definitely need to be better than we were today.
Nobody wants to play us at the moment.

When you have as much quality around the team as we do at the moment, I don't think anybody will be confident about taking us on. Let's see who we draw in the semi-final. I'm confident that, whoever it is, we'll give them a game!
You've made it to the Final. What will you need from the team now?
You always looked comfortable today after such a good win in the first leg. The Final will be a very different kind of game, though. What more will you need from your team?
We make life difficult for opponents.

I thought we looked convincing over the two legs of the semi. Whoever we meet in the Final now, they'll need to play very well indeed to make any inroads against us. The lads look well-organised and they're in fantastic form at the moment.

I thought we looked convincing over the two legs of the semi. Whoever we meet in the Final now, they'll need to play very well indeed to make any inroads against us. The lads look well-organised and they're in fantastic form at the moment.
We should be feeling confident.

I'm very excited to have made the Final. We put in two very good performances in the semi, that's for sure. This team is still developing and I think there's more to come from them. So let's wait and see.
This team's ready to take the next step.

We've played some really good football on our way to the Final. If we're going to win the trophy, I know we'll have to be even better. But I'm confident. And I'm excited. I think there's plenty more to come from this team.
You've qualified. Were you happy with the performance?
That was pretty comfortable in the end. You established a commanding lead in the first leg and now you've finished the job. What have you made of your team's performances in qualifying?
The real work starts now.

We're under no illusions. We've played well to qualify but we know there are tougher tasks ahead. The lads are under no illusions. They're going to have to be ready to face some of the best attacking players around from now on.
Qualifying was our minimum requirement.
I'm very happy with how the team's developing and we deserved to qualify. But we need to get our heads down and prepare properly. We'll face tougher challenges in the competition from now on.
We needed to qualify.

I knew that we needed to qualify for this team to keep developing. This group of players is coming together. I think they're just beginning to look like the real deal. I'm confident we'll be able to cause problems for anybody we face in the competition from now on.

I knew that we needed to qualify for this team to keep developing. This group of players is coming together. I think they're just beginning to look like the real deal. I'm confident we'll be able to cause problems for anybody we face in the competition from now on.
Disappointing today but are you pleased your boys have made it through anyway?
I'm sure you'd have wanted a better display from your team today but a commanding lead from the first leg sees you through. Were you worried your boys looked a little complacent?
It was trickier today.

We were definitely the better team over the two games. The lads were sensational in the first leg. They found it more difficult today but they kept their heads even when we went behind. That composure saw us through to the next round.
I'm glad we didn't throw it away.

I was worried today. Too many of our players just never seemed to get up to the pace of the game. We were far too loose. When we went behind, I was afraid we might fall apart. We've got plenty to work on, that's for sure.
We're through and that's what counts.

We weren't great today but, over the two legs, you have to say we deserved to go through. We must learn not to take situations for granted, though. You have to work for everything you get in football, don't you?
Were you worried you might throw a place in the semis away?
It all looked so comfortable for you after the win in the first leg. But today was a different story. You're into the semis but how close were you to throwing it away?
We kept calm.

Over the two games, I think we deserved to go through. It could have got nervy today after we went behind, but the boys always managed to stay calm. We're definitely worth our place in the semi-final.
Let's focus on our next fixture now.

Today wasn't a game to remember for us. I'm glad we managed to scrape through. At one stage it looked like we could be on the end of a big shock. Time to put that all to one side, though. We have to prepare for our next game.
We just didn't work hard enough.

That wasn't a good performance and we're grateful to have made it into the semis. We just never got going. Maybe the lads thought we could just coast through the game. I hope the boys realise it'll only get tougher from here. If we don't work harder, we've got no chance of reaching the Final.
That was tense! But you're through. What are your thoughts?
Today's defeat made it more nervous than it should have been, perhaps. Or were you always confident that big win in the first leg would be enough to get your boys into the Final?
We won it in the first leg.

The lads were brilliant in the first leg. We've got that performance to thank for our place in the Final. The game today was very tight indeed. The opposition had nothing to lose and put us under plenty of pressure. Credit to the boys for keeping their nerve.
Nobody remembers how you get to the Final!

We were great in the game at our place. Obviously we struggled here today. But we're into the Final and nobody's too worried about how we've got there. It's an occasion to look forward to for our fans.
The lads know it wasn't good enough.

We needed calm heads and discipline to keep things comfortable today. Instead, all our planning went out the window. We went chasing the ball and we got pulled out of shape. We're through but we'll have to be better in the Final, that's for sure.
Completely dominant and you're through. Pleased for the boys?
You dominated both legs of the semi-final and now you've got your reward. You can look forward to the Final now. After this display, what do you think are your chances of picking up the trophy?
We can be a match for anyone.

We've been very impressive in both legs of the semi-final and I'm glad we were able to make our quality count. We'll work hard now and I hope the lads are ready to do everything we need to be in the best possible shape for the Final now.
Let's put the Final to one side now.

Of course I'm very pleased with what I saw from my team, home and away, in this semi-final. Now, though, we have to switch our focus back to the league. We've got work to do ahead of our next game, so we'll have to put the Final to one side for the time being.
We look so secure at the moment.

I think our defensive organisation has been improving all season. You saw that in both legs of this semi. The lads are looking resolute; we use the ball intelligently and there's a good understanding developing in the team. I'm confident we've got what we need to put on a proper show in the Final.
You've qualified now. Was it ever in doubt?
Two big wins and that was more than enough to secure qualification. It'll get harder from here, but how pleased are you with how the team's playing at the moment?
We're just getting started.

Well done to the boys on a professional job. But we know it'll be more challenging from now on. Every single player will need to be on his toes, for sure. We know every team left in the competition now has players who can hurt you.
I expected nothing less!

Qualifying was an important target for us so I'm very happy with the boys. But we have a lot of football to play in the next few weeks. We need to pick up some positive results now before we turn our attention back to this competition.
You can only beat what's in front of you.

I think everybody had us down as favourites to qualify. We've done what we needed to do. Right now, we're looking very dangerous as an attacking unit and I hope scoring a few goals will have lifted the whole team. The boys will need to be at their best from now on in this competition.

I think everybody had us down as favourites to qualify. We've done what we needed to do. Right now, we're looking very dangerous as an attacking unit and I hope scoring a few goals will have lifted the whole team. The boys will need to be at their best from now on in this competition.
So, what are you expecting in the next round?
After two comfortable wins, what are you looking for now ahead of the next round? Do you still think your team has room to improve?
I think our fans will be happy we're through.

It wasn't a great spectacle but the hard work was done in the first leg. I was really pleased with how full of fight the lads were, wanting to get the job done. We stopped the opposition taking control of today's game. The fans can be happy we're through.
It's only the next game that matters now.
We played really well in the first leg. Today wasn't such a good performance but the important thing is to have made it through. Our next game is all that matters now.
We're at our best when we're positive.

I hope we've learned our lesson from this draw. We were so positive in our approach in the first leg and we won comfortably. Today, the lads looked nervy. They sat off a bit and we had to settle for the draw. The important thing, though, is we're through.
Into the semi-final. Can your team go all the way now?
The team played some very good football across these two games. You must be delighted to have reached the semi-final. Are your boys good enough to on and win the trophy now?
I'm pleased with our approach play.

In both legs of this quarter-final, I thought we looked dangerous and, of course, we scored some good goals. Some very good approach play. We'll wait to see who we get in the semis but, whoever we face, I know the lads will be able to cause them problems.
This is another small step.

We know where we want to be as a team. These two games have taken us a step further in one competition but we've got other fixtures to focus on now. We have to match these levels every time we play if we're going to achieve anything.
It's about the right frame of mind.

I'm very happy with the players' attitude over these two legs. They've shown a real winning mentality. I need that from them in every game now. We'll start thinking about the semi-final at the right time. We've other fixtures to focus on before then.
You must feel confident. How far can this team go?
You've impressed a lot of people with your last two performances in this competition. Nobody will look forward to playing you now. How far do you think your team can go?
We looked pretty dominant.

We know it'll be more challenging in the next round but I think the boys are at the top of their game right now. We're difficult to play against. We're dangerous going forward. We're confident enough to go out and dominate opponents. We can be a match for anyone.
Let's build on this.

We want to do well in every competition we enter. These two performances have shown everybody we're a decent team. I hope going through will give us the confidence to be positive in every game that we play from now on.
We've plenty to do before the next round.

We did very well to win both legs of this tie. I'm pleased with how the team is developing. It's all about consistency. We want to do well in every competition, so let's try to reach this standard in every game from now on.
